<TITLE> 41 grenades seized in Satkhira </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kamrul Hasan bdnews24.com Satkhira Correspondent Satkhira/Dhaka, Feb 15 (bdnews24.com)  The Rapid Action Battalion has seized 41 grenades in a hunt for militants believed to be hiding in Debhata upazila in the southwestern district of Satkhira, witnesses said Friday night. RAB director general Khandaker Hasan Mahmud confirmed the news of the operation to bdnews24.com by phone Friday night, but would not give further details. But several villagers told bdnews24.com that the RAB had dug out the grenades from near a pond in Shimulia village in the upazila. Nazrul Islam Gharami, a resident of Shimulia village, was arrested with alleged links to the recovery of grenades, the villagers said. Also, referring to several other villagers, Noapara Union Parishad chairman Rezaul Islam said Nazrul Islam, son of Mujibar Rahman, had been arrested. Debhata police chief Lokman Hakim told bdnews24.com that he had heard about the operation and seizure of the grenades. Meanwhile, a RAB officer, speaking by phone, invited bdnews24.com to a press conference scheduled for an 11am start at the RAB Headquarters in Dhaka Saturday. But he did not confirm if the news conference would focus on the recovery of grenades or any high-profile arrest with militant links. bdnews24.co
